        "cooked": "<p>iPhone 14 Pro Max / iOS 26.1 / version 7.86.2</p>\n<p>Hi !</p>\n<p>I don’t know if it’s a bug or if this feature isn’t working: when I forward messages from a conversation between two or three users to a group where I’m an administrator and the other two are also administrators, the forwarded messages don’t include the name of the person who originally wrote the message. I don’t know if you understand what I mean? For example, I was talking with a colleague in a one-on-one conversation (not in a group) and then I wanted to forward some messages to a group where my colleague and I are administrators to get the opinion of a third colleague who is also an administrator. But when I forward the messages from the conversation with my first colleague to the group where there are three of us, absolutely all the messages appear as having been sent by me, the one who forwarded them. This is a problem because my third colleague has difficulty understanding what’s being said since there’s no name of the person who originally wrote the message.</p>\n<p>Another missing feature is the ability to forward more than 32 messages at once. Why a maximum of 32? This forces the operation to be done in several steps, which can be a source of error and confusion.</p>\n<p>Best regards</p>",
