        "cooked": "<p>The forwarding feature currently works as designed (not a bug). I don’t know about your second feature request, but the first one is at least partially covered by the following FR:</p>\n<aside class=\"quote quote-modified\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"41974\">\n  <div class=\"title\">\n    <div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n    <img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/munikho/48/12840_2.png\" class=\"avatar\">\n    <div class=\"quote-title__text-content\">\n      <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/make-it-visually-clear-that-a-forwarded-message-was-forwarded/41974/\">Make it visually clear that a forwarded message was forwarded</a> <a class=\"badge-category__wrapper \" href=\"/c/feature-requests/17\"><span data-category-id=\"17\" style=\"--category-badge-color: #83B72A; --category-badge-text-color: #FFFFFF;\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category --style-square \" title=\"Post your ideas here for new features and functionality for the Signal app.\"><span class=\"badge-category__name\">Feature Requests</span></span></a>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <blockquote>\n    At the moment there is nothing indicating a message was forwarded. This can be rather confusing because it can seem like the person you are messaging with, wrote the forwarded message. \n[Screenshot 2022-02-18 at 10.07.33] \nIt could be helpful to have some kind of clear indication that a message is forwarded. \nNot a very original design (maybe it doesn’t have to be?), but to clarify my point: \n[Screenshot 2022-02-18 at 10.07.28]\n  </blockquote>\n</aside>\n",
